node.text: Hey guys. January is “National Slavery & Human Trafficking Prevention Month.” But the reality of  Human Trafficking is it’s a year round problem. Not just for America but all over the world. And covid is making things worse. I’m talking to @itsaliciakozak (the incredible Survivor, motivational speaker and educator) about how you can recognize a Human Trafficking situation, report it and how you can stop the spread of Child Sexual Abuse Material (CSAM) and get involved at your local level. Please ask questions below. I will do my best to answer them. And if you want to report human trafficking here is the government hotline. 1-888-373-7888. Thank you all and be safe! ❤️

I am thrilled to introduce Star Anise & Palmarosa, a bold natural deodorant scent created arm in [under]arm with @humblebrands. (Pinch me, I have an official Humble signature scent!) 

50% of the profits of this scent will benefit @TogetherWeRise, an organization dedicated to transforming the way children navigate through the foster care system in America. Through this collaboration, we have the power to help provide foster youth with the resources they need and to remind them that they matter. 

Not sponsored, just a big ol’ fan of coming together to make good things happen.

Homelessness starts rising when median rents in a region exceed 22% of median income, and rises even more sharply at 32%; in LA, the median rent is 46.7% or nearly half of median income.
It’s crucial now more than ever that we create affordable housing, increase hourly wages, and ensure that all Angelenos are safely housed. 
Explore how we can do that together at our Home Together virtual event on Thursday, April 29. (I’ll put the link in my stories and bio as well. Please join us)

RSVP: lafh.org/hometogether2021
